buildAlpha(bool,uint256,uint16,uint16,ui.details: Note that setting curPeriod to something greater than nPeriods means bond will be immediately interpreted as 'completed'.Some fields may be encoded with smaller resolution than may be apparent to decrease storage space -- these include: couponSize

params.beneficiary: Account address of recipient of all payments
params.curPeriod: Current period of the bond (usually starts at 0)
params.currencyRef: Id of currency to expect payments to be made in
params.flag: Boolean describing if bond is defaulted (usually starts as false)

returns.alp: Alpha bytes32 used to represent the first part of the bond

buildBeta(uint256,uint64,uint64,address).details: Some fields may be encoded with smaller resolution than may be apparent to decrease storage space -- these include: faceValue and periodDuration

params.faceValue: Amount to pay at end of bond
params.minter: Account address of the bond creator
params.periodDuration: How long between each period of the bond, in seconds
params.startTime: Time this bond begins at, in seconds since 1970

params.alp: Alpha part of the bond data
params.bet: Beta part of the bond data
